South Africa‘s rand weakened on Tuesday morning against a stronger dollar and amid ebbing investor enthusiasm for emerging market assets. At 06:38 the rand was 0.64% down at 12.5425 against the dollar after closing at 12.4250 on Monday. Bonds fell, with the yield on the benchmark government bond due in 2026 up 4.5 basis point to 8.485. The Johannesburg Stock Exchange opened lower with the Top-40 index down 0.5% shortly after the opening bell.